methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for adding a label.

params.name: addr
params.comment: address where the label is to be added.

params.name: name
params.comment:
name of the new label. A null name will cause a default label
 be added.

params.name: namespace
params.comment: the namespace of the label. (i.e. the namespace this label is associated with)

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructs a new command for adding a label.

params.name: addr
params.comment: address where the label is to be added.

params.name: name
params.comment:
name of the new label. A null name will cause a default label
 be added.

params.name: useLocalNamespace
params.comment:
If true, the namespace will be that of the lowest level namespace
 for the indicated address. If false, the global namespace is used for the namespace.

params.name: source
params.comment: the source of this symbol: Symbol.DEFAULT, Symbol.IMPORTED, Symbol.ANALYSIS, or Symbol.USER_DEFINED.
